課程概述 Course Description
       1 

課程學習目標 Course Objectives    
	    The course explores the fundamentals and applications of the high-frequency resonant, quasi resonant and multi-resonant power conversion techniques. And then, the characteristics of the zero-voltage and zero-current switching techniques in pulse-width modulation converters and inverters are introduced. Finally, pulse-width modulation and frequency modulation; non-linear analysis techniques for resonant and soft-switching converters and inverters; power factor correction rectifiers and distributed power systems are studied.    

